  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "Unfollowing people on Instagram quickly can streamline your feed and reduce clutter. Here are some steps to efficiently unfollow people:\n\n1. **Unfollow Directly from Your Following List**:\n   - Open the Instagram app and go to your profile by tapping on your profile picture in the bottom right.\n   - Tap on the \"Following\" count at the top of your profile to see the list of people you're following.\n   - Scroll through the list and, for each account you want to unfollow, tap the \"Following\" button next to their name. It will turn into \"Follow\", indicating you've unfollowed them.\n\n2. **Use \"Least Interacted With\" or \"Most Shown in Feed\" Categories**:\n   - Instagram sometimes categorizes your follows. Go to your \"Following\" list.\n   - At the top, you might see categories such as \"Least Interacted With\". Tap on it to see the list of those accounts and unfollow as needed.\n\n3. **Utilize Batch Unfollowing Apps**:\n   - There are third-party apps available on app stores that allow you to manage your Instagram followers and followings more efficiently. Apps like \"Cleaner for Instagram\" or \"Unfollow for Instagram\" might help.\n   - Be cautious when using third-party apps due to privacy concerns and potential violations of Instagram's terms of service.\n\n4. **Clean Up Your Feed**:\n   - As you go through your feed, if you come across posts from someone you want to unfollow, you can do so directly by tapping on their profile, and then tapping the \"Following\" button to unfollow them.\n\n5. **Unfollow from their Profile**:\n   - If you know specific accounts you want to unfollow, search for them directly using the search bar.\n   - Once on their profile, tap on the \"Following\" button to unfollow them.\n\nInstagram limits the number of unfollows you can do in a short time span, so if you're unfollowing many accounts, you may need to take breaks to avoid being temporarily blocked from performing this action.",
